history.content: did this schedule last spring with a similar-difficulty fall schedule and i thought it worked well! data 100 and 188 don't have workloads that are too high, you mostly just have to make sure you're prepared for the exams. 170 has long problem sets but they're not any worse than 70's.

children.subject:
1. Yeah, I'd say it's pretty similar! NGL I put less effort into 170, but I also did worse on the assignments as a result so..

2. I'd say it's very similar to Data 8's, although the material is a little harder so it takes slightly more time.

3. I haven't taken 16B yet (rip @ next semester), but if it's worse than 70, nothing in that schedule is worse.

4. It's more of a coding class -- projects are fill-in-the-blank Python kinda like 61A projects -- with 61C-esque Gradescope homeworks. The exams are more in-between, since it's a heavily theory-based class.
188 does have weekly written in addition to electronic hw tho!

Haha don’t mean to scare you with 16B for sure especially since I’m taking it with sahai right now and he isn’t teaching it next semester. But still definitely long Psets. But back to the point, this helps a lot and I do think I feel comfy taking all 3 of those and my breadth class at the same time. I hope i don’t regret this. Thanks so much for the input!

Hi anon, thanks so much for the reply! Based on what you said I do have a few follow ups:

1. Would you consider 170 a similar workload to 70?

2. For data 100, would you say the labs/hws/projects (in terms of time committment) are along the lines of 61AB's or Data 8's corresponding labs/hws/projects

3. Nothing is as long as 16B psets right? Because they are death and really taking time away from allowing to fully absorb material in other classes. 70 Psets are difficult for sure, but not insanely time consuming like 16B. 

4. I've heard mixed things: is 188 a "Pset" class like 170/70, or a coding class like 61AB? 

Thanks for the clarifications in advance!
